ustralian politician)}} || {{Australian party style|Labor}}|&nbsp; || [[Australian Labor Party|Labor]] || New South Wales || 1965 || 1958, 1959\u20131970\n|-\n|| {{sort|OSullivan, Neil|Hon. [[Neil O'Sullivan]]}} || {{Australian party style|Liberal}}|&nbsp; || [[Liberal Party of Australia|Liberal]] || Queensland || 1962 || 1947\u20131962\n|-\n|| {{sort|Paltridge, Shane|Hon [[Shane Paltridge]]}} || {{Australian party style|Liberal}}|&nbsp; || [[Liberal Party of Australia|Liberal]] || Western Australia || 1962 || 1951\u20131966\n|-\n|| {{sortname|Rex|Pearson}} {{efn|name=Pearson|Liberal Senator [[Rex Pearson]] died on 11 September 1961; Liberal member [[Gordon Davidson (Australian politician)|Gordon Davidson]] was appointed to fill the ensuing vacancy on 28 September. He did not stand at the [[1961 Australian federal election|9 December 1961 election]] and his position was won by Liberal candidate [[Nancy Buttfield]]. In order to take up the seat with a term finishing on 30 June 1965, Buttfield resigned her pre-existing seat won at the [[1955 Australian federal election|1955 election]] and scheduled to expire on 30 June 1962; Davidson was appointed to that position on 8 February 1962.}} || {{Australian party style|Liberal}}|&nbsp; || [[Liberal Party of Australia|Liberal]] || South Australia || 1965 || 1951\u20131961\n|-\n|| {{sortname|Bob|Poke}} || {{Australian party style|Labor}}|&nbsp; || [[Australian Labor Party|Labor]] || Tasmania || 1962 || 1956\u20131974\n|-\n|| {{sortname|Dame Annabelle|Rankin|Annabelle Rankin|Rankin, Annabelle}} || {{Australian party style|Liberal}}|&nbsp; || [[Liberal Party of Australia|Liberal]] || Queensland || 1962 || 1947\u20131971\n|-\n|| {{sortname|Albert|Reid}} || {{Australian party style|National}}|&nbsp; || [[National Party of Australia|Country]] || New South Wales || 1962 || 1950\u20131962\n|-\n|| {{sortname|Clem|Ridley}} || {{Australian party style|Labor}}|&nbsp; || [[Australian Labor Party|Labor]] || South Australia || 1965 || 1959